tweet_raw: The Objective of #Starlink  Starlink constitutes SpaceXs unique constellation of satellites engineered to deliver low-latency internet access across the entire globe.Conventional satellite internet relies on large satellites with extended operational lifespans typically spanning 15 years or more. These satellites are stationed in geostationary orbits approximately 35800 kilometers (22245 miles) above the Earths surface directly over the equator. This arrangement allows only a limited number of satellites to cover the majority of the planet.However because of their high orbital positions the time it takes for signals to travel to and from these satellites is prolonged approximately 550 milliseconds. This delay poses a hindrance for current satellite internet providers in offering the kind of low-latency high-speed internet that Starlink aspires to deliver.There is no #QFS without - Starlink
